<br>
I've played AO since Beta, and have played 10 of the 13 professions to at least level 100, and the remaining 2 to at least level 50.<br>
<br>
MAs are hands down the best solo class around.<br>
<br>
I have defined 3 personal key ingredients to being able to solo &quot;successfully&quot; in AO:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>1) Healing</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
Without healing you really have a hard time soloing effectively.  Some classes can <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>almost</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> compensate for this with Calms (Mezzing), but healing is superior to calms for the most part when it comes to solo play.<br>
<br>
MAs have decent enough heal nanos to solo, and don't have to spend a lot of &quot;downtime&quot; between fights sitting and recharging health AND nano since they can simply heal theselves as they go.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>2) Damage over time</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
If it takes you ~1 minute to kill an even-con mob, it will take you nearly an hour to complete an entire solo mission.  The faster you can take down your opponents, the faster you will level, and the less you will feel that you are just &quot;spinning your wheels&quot; and getting nowhere on the levelling treadmill.  Example: Low level soldiers have NO healing, and their damage over time is not great (at lower levels).  Even though I twinked him out, leveling my soldier from 3-30 was painfully tedious and took nearly a week.  I leveled my MA from 3-30 in about 2 days, and my NT, Enforcer, Fixer and Adventurer in about 3 days.<br>
<br>
MAs have the best PvM damage over time (hands down) due to their superfast fist speed and devastating critical buffs.<br>
<br>
The combination of self-healing and the best damage over time makes MAs the easiest to solo.  But what about &quot;most fun&quot; solo class?  That brings us to versatility...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>3) Versatility</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
In my experience, the more versatile a class is, the more fun it is to play.  And while MAs definitely lack versatility, they make up for it somewhat by excelling in the first 2 points (ie, it's ALWAYS fun to kick ass and take names).  However, an example of a truly versatile profession would be Fixer or Trader.  Fixers get fast, uber weapons (SMGs) with specials (burst, area burst, etc), and have some VERY fun abilities.  Just look at their nanos: Roots, Snares, HoTs, NCU buffs, awesome Run Speed buffs, nice Damage buffs, grid evacs, fixer grid, and if you are lucky and/or grotesquely wealthy there's always Grid Armor.  Traders are equally blessed with versatility: their weapon-of-choice (the Shotgun) is extremely potent, they have green tradeskills, and their nanos include: Awesome drains, weapon skill wrangles, roots, CALMS, awesome trade skill buffs, team heals, etc.  In addition, both of these professions are wanted by teams and are very capable in PvP (even though you said that wasn't important in your case).<br>
<br>
So I can tell you first-hand that while MAs are the most <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>efficient</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> at solo play, you may give Fixers or Traders a shot as an alt if you find yourself getting a little bored with just doing uber damage and plowing through missions non-stop.  <br>
<br>
Of course, every person is different, so it kinda depends on what you are looking to do in AO.  But if blowing through solo missions and crushing all mobs that stand in your way as you level up is your primary goal, MA is almost certainly the way to go.<br>
<br>
- iccusion<br>
<br>
